# Dart Mobile Game Studio (broad rule)

For any Dart / Flutter **mobile game** work, use the **dart-mobile-game-studio** skill. Canonical:
`.agents/skills/dart-mobile-game-studio/SKILL.md` (Cursor copy: `.cursor/skills/...`). Ground
decisions in the official Flutter org — **flutter/games** (Casual Games Toolkit) and
**flame-engine/flame**.

Builds simple 2D games for iOS + Android: coloring, puzzles, platformers, drag-and-drop,
memory/matching, lite runners, tap-reaction, educational mini-games.

## Always follow this workflow
1. Understand (genre, age, core verb, fail model, platforms, orientation).
2. One-page Mini-GDD (`assets/gdd-template.md`).
3. Choose mode: **Flutter-widgets-only** (CustomPainter) / **Flame** (FlameGame) / **hybrid**
   (`GameWidget` + overlays). Decision rule: `references/flutter-game-architecture.md`.
4. Architecture: **pure Dart core (no `package:flutter` import)** + state machine + thin widgets/Flame.
5. Implement a small MVP from `assets/flame_game_template.dart` / `assets/flutter_game_widget_template.dart`.
6. Tests: `dart test` for the model; `flutter_test` for widgets; Patrol for E2E.
7. Build/test with `dart analyze` / `dart test` / `flutter test` / `flutter build` when available.
8. Review: `scripts/dart-doctor.py`, kids/privacy/a11y/perf (`references/quality-policy.md`).
9. Hand off: changed files, commands run + output, assumptions, risks.

## Non-negotiables
- No copyrighted assets — placeholder vector art (`CustomPainter`/`flutter_svg`) or user-owned only.
- Game rules in pure Dart (no Flutter imports), unit-tested; UI/business/game-logic separated.
- Minimal dependencies via `references/package-policy.md` (justify each).
- `flutter analyze`-clean, `dart format`, null-safe, `const`, dispose everything.
- Accessibility via `Semantics` (label/value/button); text scaling; reduce motion.
- Kids apps: no tracking/analytics/ads/AdvertisingId/external-links/accounts; offline-first; must
  satisfy **both** Apple Kids and Google Play Families. Monetization only for general (13+) builds
  per `references/monetization-policy.md`.
- Never claim store approval — give a checklist and risks (`references/release-policy.md`).
- Don't mix Flutter-UI and Flame in one screen without the decision rule.

